**Long-Acting Reversible Contraception (LARC):**

**Levonorgestrel IUDs:**

| Device | Dose | Size | Duration |
|--------|------|------|----------|
| Mirena | 52 mg | 32x32 mm | 6 years |
| Liletta | 52 mg | 32x32 mm | 6 years |
| Kyleena | 19.5 mg | 28x30 mm | 5 years |
| Skyla | 13.5 mg | 28x30 mm | 3 years |

**Mechanism:**
- Thickens cervical mucus
- Suppresses ovulation in some cycles
- Thins endometrium
- Local progestin effect

**Placement:**
- Speculum examination
- Tenaculum to stabilize cervix
- Sound uterus to measure depth
- Insert through cervical canal
- Strings trimmed

**Follow-up:**
- Check placement in 4-6 weeks
- Strings visible at cervix
- Self-check for strings

**Copper IUD (Paragard, T380A):**
- Copper ions inhibit sperm motility
- Inhibits egg implantation
- Non-hormonal
- 10+ years duration

**Implant (Nexplanon):**
- Single rod, 4 cm long
- Subdermal insertion
- Etonogestrel 68 mg
- 5 years duration
- Inserted with special applicator

**Combined Hormonal Contraceptives:**

**Pill Formulations:**

| Type | Estrogen | Progestin | Pills per pack |
|------|----------|-----------|----------------|
| Monophasic | Fixed | Fixed | 21/28 or 28 |
| Biphasic | Varies | Varies | 28 |
| Triphasic | Varies | Varies | 28 |
| 24/4 | Fixed | Fixed | 28 |
| 91-day | Fixed | Fixed | 91 |

**Progestins:**
- Norethindrone, norethindrone acetate
- Ethynodiol diacetate
- Levonorgestrel
- Norgestimate, norgestrel
- Drospirenone
- Nomegestrol acetate

**Patch (Xulane):**
- 20 cm² patch
- Release 150 mcg norelgestromin, 35 mcg EE daily
- Apply weekly for 3 weeks, then 1 week off
- Apply to clean, dry skin (buttock, abdomen, back, upper arm)
- Rotate sites

**Ring (NuvaRing, Annovera):**
- Soft, flexible ring
- Vaginal insertion
- Left in place for 3 weeks
- Remove, wait 1 week, insert new ring
- Can use continuously for no periods

**Barrier Methods:**

**Male Condoms:**
- Latex or polyurethane
- Rolled onto erect penis
- Leave space at tip
- Withdraw while still erect
- Dispose after use

**Female Condom:**
- Polyurethane sheath
- Inserted prior to intercourse
- External ring covers labia
- Internal ring covers cervix
- Removed after intercourse

**Diaphragm:**
- Dome-shaped silicone or latex
- Rim covers cervix
- Used with spermicide
- Left in place for 6 hours after intercourse
- Must be fitted by healthcare provider
- Can be used multiple times with proper care

**Cervical Cap:**
- Thimble-shaped
- Fits over cervix
- Different sizes available
- Used with spermicide
- Left in place for 6 hours after intercourse
- Must be fitted

**Sponge (Today Sponge):**
- Polyurethane sponge
- Contains nonoxynol-9 (spermicide)
- Fits over cervix
- Effective for 24 hours of multiple acts of intercourse
- Available OTC

**Fertility Awareness Methods:**

| Method | What's Tracked |
|--------|---------------|
| Temperature | Basal body temperature |
| Cervical mucus | Consistency changes |
| Calendar | Cycle days |
| Symptothermal | Combination of methods |

- TwoDay Method:
- Cervical mucus monitoring
- Abstain during secretory days
- 12-day fertile window

- Standard Days Method:
- Calendar-based
- Days 8-19 of cycle fertile
- For cycles 26-32 days only

- Basal Body Temperature:
- Take temperature first thing in morning
- Shift up after ovulation
- Abstain until 3 days after shift
- Requires consistent sleep patterns

**Withdrawal:**
- Penis withdrawn before ejaculation
- Pre-ejaculation may contain sperm
- High failure rate due to difficulty with timing
- Requires high self-control
